    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nAdds q-head padding for `flashmla_kv` to support pure-TP configurations. FlashMLA requires q heads to be 64 or 128, but with tensor parallelism the per-GPU head count gets divided (e.g., GLM-5's 64 heads / TP8 = 8 heads; DeepSeek V3.2's 128 heads / TP8 = 16 heads). When using TP+DP attention, the effective attention TP size is 1, so no padding is needed. We pad to the next supported variant (64/128) for pure-TP cases and slice the output back. Also updates Hopper FP8 default from `flashmla_auto` to `flashmla_kv` since the former unconditionally resolves to the latter on SM90 (heuristic switching only happens on Blackwell).\r\n\r\n## Accuracy Test\r\n\r\n```\r\nsglang serve \\\r\n  --model-path zai-org/GLM-5.1-FP8 \\\r\n  --tensor-parallel-size 8 \\\r\n  --enable-flashinfer-allreduce-fusion \\\r\n  --kv-cache-dtype fp8_e4m3 \\\r\n  --reasoning-parser glm45 \\\r\n  --tool-call-parser glm47 \\\r\n  --speculative-algorithm EAGLE \\\r\n  --speculative-num-steps 3 \\\r\n  --speculative-eagle-topk 1 \\\r\n  --speculative-num-draft-tokens 4 \\\r\n  --model-loader-extra-config '{\"enable_multithread_load\": true, \"num_threads\": 142}'\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\npython benchmark/gsm8k/bench_sglang.py --num-shots 20 --num-questions 1319 --parallel 1319\r\n\r\n100%|█████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████████| 1319/1319 [03:11<00:00,  6.89it/s]\r\nAccuracy: 0.958\r\nInvalid: 0.000\r\nLatency: 191.442 s\r\nOutput throughput: 751.434 token/s\r\n```",
